import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], errors='ignore')
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], errors='ignore')
    
    plt.plot(data['budgetYear'], data['value'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the trend of budget values over the years?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
